{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"81fa1680-93c0-413a-99f1-e7d369b035f9","content":"Use `dotnet watch` to get hot reload. It re-runs tests automatically whenever you save a file:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. **Watch** all `.cs` and `.csproj` files for changes\n2. **Re-run** the filtered test automatically on each save\n3. Support **hot reload** for most code changes (no full rebuild needed)\n\nSince your project uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (via `global.json`), `dotnet watch` works out of the box. Just edit `InventoryServiceTests.cs`, save, and the test re-executes instantly.\n\n> **Tip:** Drop the `--filter` flag to run all tests on each save if you want broader coverage.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ebe2297d-3848-4aba-88fa-6e1a18ef27d0","outputTokens":188},"id":"8dc463e6-bb05-40ea-8b11-9b95c0a93487","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:48.900Z","parentId":"a08e19c0-02f8-43c5-a2d5-89181faf47ea"}
